Police say McGee told the woman she would show the explicit photographs to her family and friends if she did not participate in sex acts for money.

McGee advertised the woman's services on social media, and clients would meet her at the home she shared with McGee.

The landlord of McGee, also her neighbor, said she didn't notice anything untoward occurring at the home.

"[I'm] totally surprised. We had no inkling at all that anything was going on over there," Sharon Lawton told CBC News.

Lawton said McGee told her that the 18-year-old was her young cousin.

